    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Flat puppets of leather or another material, often elaborately painted, originally developed in Java to cast shadows on white screens during dramatizations in shadow theater. They are often, but not always, animated with rods.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Títeres cuidadosamente pintados, usualmente de cuero liso, originalmente desarrollados en Java para proyectar sombras sobre mamparas blancas durante las dramatizaciones.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
